<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <title>PopForge</title>

    <meta
      name="description"
      content="PopForge is a cross-platform GUI for converting PlayStation 1 disc images to EBOOT.PBP files for PSP and PS Vita."
    />

    <meta property="og:title" content="PopForge" />
    <meta property="og:description" content="PSX to EBOOT, forged for every platform." />
    <meta property="og:type" content="website" />

    <link rel="icon" href="./icon.svg" type="image/svg+xml" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="./styles.css" />
  </head>

  <body>
    <main class="page">
      <section class="hero">
        <div class="hero-icon">
          <img src="./icon.svg" alt="PopForge icon" />
        </div>

        <div class="hero-copy">
          <p class="eyebrow">PSX · PSP · Vita</p>
          <h1>PopForge</h1>
          <p class="tagline">PSX to EBOOT, forged for every platform.</p>

          <p class="description">
            A simple cross-platform desktop app for converting PlayStation 1
            disc images to <strong>EBOOT.PBP</strong> files playable on PSP and
            PS Vita through Adrenaline.
          </p>

          <div class="actions">
            <a class="button primary disabled" href="#downloads" aria-disabled="true">
              Coming Soon
            </a>

            <a class="button" href="#features">
              View Features
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="panel" id="features">
        <h2>Features</h2>

        <div class="feature-grid">
          <article class="feature">
            <h3>ISO / BIN+CUE to EBOOT</h3>
            <p>Convert PS1 disc images into PSP-compatible EBOOT.PBP files.</p>
          </article>

          <article class="feature">
            <h3>Auto Game ID Detection</h3>
            <p>Detects PlayStation game IDs automatically when possible.</p>
          </article>

          <article class="feature">
            <h3>Batch Queue</h3>
            <p>Queue multiple games and monitor progress for each conversion.</p>
          </article>

          <article class="feature">
            <h3>PBP Extraction</h3>
            <p>Extract existing EBOOT.PBP files back into disc image format.</p>
          </article>

          <article class="feature">
            <h3>Filename Templates</h3>
            <p>Format output names using tokens like %GAMEID%, %TITLE%, and %REGION%.</p>
          </article>

          <article class="feature">
            <h3>Cross Platform</h3>
            <p>Built for macOS, Windows, and Linux using Tauri and Svelte.</p>
          </article>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="panel" id="downloads">
        <h2>Downloads</h2>

        <div class="downloads">
          <span>macOS Apple Silicon</span>
          <span>Windows</span>
          <span>Linux</span>
        </div>

        <p class="note">
          Downloads will be available once the first public release is ready.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="panel">
        <h2>Built on retro foundations</h2>

        <p>
          PopForge wraps
          <a href="https://github.com/pseiler/popstationr">popstationr</a>,
          a lightweight command-line tool for creating PSP-compatible PS1 EBOOT files.
        </p>

        <p>
          The project is also inspired by
          <a href="https://github.com/RupertAvery/PSXPackager">PSXPackager</a>,
          especially its batch processing and packaging workflow.
        </p>
      </section>

      <footer class="footer">
        <p>
          PopForge is currently in development. Public release coming soon.
        </p>
      </footer>
    </main>
  </body>
</html>
